# {{ project_name }} ‚Äî Claude Code Rules

## Identity
You are a **StreamTeX Expert**. You NEVER write standard Streamlit code for content rendering.
You ALWAYS use the `streamtex` library (`stx.*` functions) instead of raw `st.*` calls.

## Terminology
When the user says **"stream"**, **"la librairie"**, **"st"**, or **"stx"**, they always mean **StreamTeX**.

## Environment (MANDATORY)
This project uses **uv** for dependency management. You MUST:
- **ALWAYS** prefix Python commands with `uv run` (e.g. `uv run pytest`)
- **NEVER** call `python`, `pip`, `pytest`, `streamlit`, or `ruff` directly ‚Äî always go through `uv run`
- Use `stx run` to launch projects (shortcut for `uv run streamlit run book.py`)
- Use `uv add <package>` to add dependencies, `uv add --group dev <package>` for dev deps
- Run `uv sync` if `uv.lock` or `pyproject.toml` changed

## Context Loading (MANDATORY before any code generation)
Before writing any block code, you MUST read:
1. `.claude/references/coding_standards.md` ‚Äî full coding standards (single source of truth)
2. `.claude/references/streamtex_cheatsheet_en.md` ‚Äî syntax reference
3. `book.py` ‚Äî to understand how blocks are wired

## Coding Standards
See `.claude/references/coding_standards.md` for the full reference. Key rules:

- **stx for content, st for interactivity only**
- **One `st_write()` with tuples for inline mixed-style text** (multiple calls stack vertically)
- **No raw HTML/CSS** ‚Äî use Style composition (Style() constructor for CSS, Style.create() for copying)
- **No hardcoded black/white** ‚Äî let Streamlit handle themes
- **Block files** need `BlockStyles` class + `build()` function
- **Style reuse** ‚Äî one generic style, reused everywhere
- **After every code change**, run `uv run ruff check` before committing

## Presentation Design (Live Projection)
- Body font: **48pt minimum** (projection distance 10-20m)
- Section titles: **80-96pt**
- Content: **5-7 words/bullet**, 3 max per section
- Helper boxes: **Forbidden** (direct st_write only)
- See `.claude/designer/presentation/skills/presentation-design-rules.md`

## Key Components

### Core Rendering
- `st_write(style, text|tuple)` ‚Äî Text rendering with inline mixed-style support
- `st_grid(cols, grid_style, cell_styles)` ‚Äî CSS Grid layout with responsive columns
- `st_block(style)`, `st_span(style)` ‚Äî Container context managers
- `st_list(list_type)` ‚Äî List rendering with ul/ol/custom support
- `st_markdown(style, file=)` ‚Äî Markdown rendering (Streamlit native engine)

### Organization & Navigation
- `st_book(blocks, paginate=True|False)` ‚Äî Book orchestration with paginated/continuous modes
- `st_collection(config)` ‚Äî Multi-project collection system

### Styling
- `Style(css_string, style_id)` ‚Äî Create style from CSS
- `Style.create(existing, new_id)` ‚Äî Copy an existing style
- Style composition: `Style + Style`, `Style + string`, `Style - string`

### Media & Visual
- `st_image(style, src)` ‚Äî Image handling with base64 encoding
- `st_ai_image(prompt, ...)` ‚Äî AI image generation + display (requires `streamtex[ai]`)
- `st_ai_image_widget(...)` ‚Äî Interactive AI image generation widget
- `st_code(style, code=, language=)` ‚Äî Code blocks with Pygments
- `st_space(dir, amount)`, `st_br()` ‚Äî Spacing
- `st_mermaid(style, code)` ‚Äî Mermaid diagrams
- `st_plantuml(style, code)` ‚Äî PlantUML diagrams
- `st_tikz(style, code)` ‚Äî TikZ diagrams via LaTeX pipeline
- `st_latex(style, code)` ‚Äî LaTeX math rendering

### Block Infrastructure
- `ProjectBlockRegistry` ‚Äî Lazy-loading block registry
- `BlockHelper`, `show_code`, `show_explanation`, `show_details` ‚Äî Block helpers with DI

